-- Citi hires Trip Wolfe as venture capital banker: memo
-- 
-- Fri May 20, 2011 9:59am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/20/us-citigroup-hire-idUSTRE74J3N320110520

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc ( C.N ) has hired Trip Wolfe to head venture capital coverage for North America within the bank's technology, media and telecoms group, according to an internal memo obtained by Reuters on Thursday. 

 Wolfe joins Citi from Union Square Advisors where he ran the firm's venture capital and private equity sponsor coverage. Prior to joining Union Square Advisors, he worked at Bank of America, Jefferies & Company and Deutsche Bank. Wolfe will take a newly created role within Citigroup to help boost client relationships in the venture capital and related private equity communities, according to the memo. Citigroup spokesman was not immediately available for comment. (Reporting by  Nadia Damouni ; writing by  Soyoung Kim ; editing by Gerald E. McCormick) (This story has been modified to correct the spelling of the name of Citigroup's new hire Trip Wolfe in the headline)